# Python style — project-specific

> **Pre-existing project rule.** The ai-orchestra has no ownership of this file and must record it in the existing-infra inventory but never overwrite, append to, or rename it.

## Conventions

- Use the app factory pattern (`create_app()`); never `app = FastAPI()` at module top level.
- Pydantic models live in `app/models.py` (or domain-specific files under `app/`).
- Public functions and methods carry type hints. Private helpers may omit them when the type is obvious from a one-line implementation.
- Imports ordered by `ruff` configuration; do not hand-edit import order.

## Validation expectation

This file's mere presence verifies that the ai-orchestra's existing-infra inventory correctly identifies a project-owned `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` file (per [`../../../../core/discovery/existing-infra.md`](../../../../core/discovery/existing-infra.md)) and the install plan emits `action: skip` for this exact path. Any plan that touches this file is a critical bug.
